IoT Gateway Support for Yocto BSP
=================================

To setup the BSP you need to have `repo` installed. Install the `repo` utility:

$ mkdir ~/bin
$ curl http://commondatastorage.googleapis.com/git-repo-downloads/repo  > ~/bin/repo
$ chmod a+x ~/bin/repo
$ PATH=${PATH}:~/bin

Create the BSP directory:

$ mkdir iotg
$ cd iotg
$ repo init -u git://git.freescale.com/imx/fsl-arm-yocto-bsp.git -b imx-4.1.15-1.0.0_iotg-demo [-m <manifest>]

<manifest>      Description
default.xml     v1.0.1.xml (this is the default if no manifest is specified)
v1.0.1.xml      Compatible with IoT Gateway with Thread SDK 1.0.0
v1.1.0.xml      Compatible with IoT Gateway with Thread SDK 1.1.0

Download the BSP:

$ repo sync

Consult the README-iotg for more information:

$ less README-iotg
